    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 15,
        "summary": "A soft answer turns away wrath\u2014A wise son makes a glad father\u2014The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the Lord\u2014Before honor comes humility.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "A soft answer turneth away wrath: but grievous words stir up anger.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience; Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 26:22 (17\u201322).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright: but the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness; Gossip.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The eyes of the Lord are in every place, beholding the evil and the good.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wholesome tongue is a tree of life: but perverseness therein is a breach in the spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty; Profanity.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool despiseth his father's instruction: but he that regardeth reproof is prudent.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:1; D&C 68:31.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:18.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In the house of the righteous is much treasure: but in the revenues of the wicked is trouble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The lips of the wise disperse knowledge: but the heart of the foolish doeth not so.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the Lord: but the prayer of the upright is his delight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:5; Moro. 7:8 (5\u201311). TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the Lord: but he loveth him that followeth after righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Correction is grievous unto him that forsaketh the way: and he that hateth reproof shall die.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 16:2; 2\u00a0Ne. 1:26; 9:40; Mosiah 13:7.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reproof.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:12.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hell and destruction are before the Lord: how much more then the hearts of the children of men?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A scorner loveth not one that reproveth him: neither will he go unto the wise.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance: but by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:22.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cheerful.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorrow.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The heart of him that hath understanding seeketh knowledge: but the mouth of fools feedeth on foolishness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:6. TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "All the days of the afflicted are evil: but he that is of a merry heart hath a continual feast.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Better is little with the fear of the Lord than great treasure and trouble therewith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 37:16; Eccl. 4:6; James 2:5 (1\u20139).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Better is a dinner of herbs where love is, than a stalled ox and hatred therewith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:1. TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0fattened ox.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wrathful man stirreth up strife: but he that is slow to anger appeaseth strife.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:29.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of the slothful man is as an hedge of thorns: but the way of the righteous is made plain.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 827
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise son maketh a glad father: but a foolish man despiseth his mother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:1.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Motherhood.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Folly is joy to him that is destitute of wisdom: but a man of understanding walketh uprightly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Without counsel purposes are disappointed: but in the multitude of counsellors they are established.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:28; Jacob 4:10; Alma 37:12; D&C 105:37; 122:2.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man hath joy by the answer of his mouth: and a word spoken in due season, how good is it!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:11.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 3:1 (1\u20138).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of life is above to the wise, that he may depart from hell beneath.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:2; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:39.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord will destroy the house of the proud: but he will establish the border of the widow.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 12:7; D&C 64:24.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 146:9.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the Lord: but the words of the pure are pleasant words.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is greedy of gain troubleth his own house; but he that hateth gifts shall live.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The heart of the righteous studieth to answer: but the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Study.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord is far from the wicked: but he heareth the prayer of the righteous.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 10:1.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 11:24 (23\u201325); 21:15; D&C 101:7.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart: and a good report maketh the bones fat.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The ear that heareth the reproof of life abideth among the wise.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that refuseth instruction despiseth his own soul: but he that heareth reproof getteth understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0obeys.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord is the instruction of wisdom; and before honour is humility.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honor.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}